President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State to provide assistance for refugees, victims of conflict, and other individuals at risk due to the situation in Afghanistan. The memorandum grants the Secretary of State the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $200,000,000 in articles and services from any agency of the United States Government and military education and training from the Department of Defense. Additionally, the Secretary of State is authorized to make the necessary determination and notifications to Congress before any drawdown takes place. The memorandum is to be published in the Federal Register.